      <body>Rake doesn't show tasks without descriptions by default.

From http://rake.rubyforge.org/files/doc/rakefile_rdoc.html:

&gt; Only tasks with descriptions will be displayed with the &quot;-T&quot; switch. Use &quot;-P&quot; (or &quot;&#8212;prereqs&quot;) to get a list of all tasks and their prerequisites.

So, if you want to see tasks without descriptions, use `-P`. I'm making this one as invalid since this is intended behavior.

Thanks for reporting! :)</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Rake doesn't show tasks without descriptions by default.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From &lt;a href=
&quot;http://rake.rubyforge.org/files/doc/rakefile_rdoc.html&quot;&gt;http://rake.rubyforge.org/files/doc/rakefile_rdoc.html&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Only tasks with descriptions will be displayed with the &quot;-T&quot;
switch. Use &quot;-P&quot; (or &quot;&amp;#8212;prereqs&quot;) to get a list of all tasks
and their prerequisites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, if you want to see tasks without descriptions, use
&lt;code&gt;-P&lt;/code&gt;. I'm making this one as invalid since this is
intended behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting! :)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
